# Requests

**Requests** is a simple, yet elegant HTTP library.

```python
>>> import requests
>>> r = requests.get('https://api.github.com/user', auth=('user', 'pass'))
>>> r.status_code
200
>>> r.headers['content-type']
'application/json; charset=utf8'
>>> r.encoding
'utf-8'
>>> r.text
'{"type":"User"...'
>>> r.json()
{'disk_usage': 368627, 'private_gists': 484, ...}
```

Requests allows you to send HTTP/1.1 requests extremely easily. There’s
no need to manually add query strings to your URLs, or to form-encode your
`PUT` & `POST` data — but nowadays, just use the `json` method!

Requests is one of the most downloaded Python package today, pulling in
around `14M downloads / week`— according to GitHub, Requests is currently
[depended upon] by `500,000+` repositories. You may certainly put your
trust in this code.

